Text: What we achieved.
We had two team meetings to go over work we had done and made progress finishing up everything in each part of the process.
This meant finishing off the ETL pipeline, database and mapping.
The good.
As a team we did a better job of meeting up to discuss what we had done and collaborating on tasks.
I have also gotten a better sense of how people work.
Roro finished off the database and contributed to the code for processing the data and Bibi has been working on the front end of the project.
I've done a better job of contributing to the project suggesting ideas and asking more questions for things I need clarification on.
I'm a little more comfortable with my own working style and I do not feel like I need to keep up with faster coders as long as I am working consistently on the project.
Things to improve on as a team.
This week has been the best week so far, as we have done a better job of communicating.
However, I'm not sure how Kuku feels at the moment with the project.
He was supposed to be working on the front end with Bibi but I feel neither of them have taken the initiative to keep in touch with each other.
I think that Kuku may feel he has not contributed enough, as Bibi is able to do most tasks by himself.
As a team we could be even more open with our communication, to keep everyone in the loop and ask if anyone needs any help.
I've also talked to Roro about this and told him we need to help each other out a bit further.

Judging from our conversations since then, I believe he has realised he may have rushed into solutions too quickly without going over with the team what each person really wanted to do in the project.
I don't think Roro meant any harm in the way he jumped into things, it's probably more because he loves to solve problems.
I feel the downside of this is some of our team mates may have felt a bit alienated.

To improve this we will need to continue to be more open with our communication and I feel we may need to have a chat about how each member has felt about the project, to hopefully learn what we could have done better in the initial stages.
Things I could do better.
I need to do a better job with checking in with team members individually to see if they need a hand with work or if they are unsure with what they are doing.
This would help keep each team member engaged with the project and hopefully build some team spirit.
I also feel I could do a better job of being a bit more assertive about setting goals each week for the team and myself to make sure we have all the pieces together.
Goals for next week.
Next week, I'll continue setting up meetings for the team and try to set up a schedule for tasks that need to be done over the week.
I will also aim to check in with individual team mates to see how they are doing.
On the technical side, I will be helping put all our transformation functions online to a Jupyter notebook and testing to see if we are able to process everything in our ETL pipeline.
I will also get my ideas together for my final report, I'm leaning towards doing a user manual but will have to have a better look through to confirm.
General thoughtsÂ .
The biggest lessons in this project have been related to dealing with different personalities in the team.
The last team I was in was very communicative and very engaged in the project which meant the biggest hurdles were figuring what to do and how to do them.
The biggest challenge so far in this project have been getting people to step up and own their part of the project and communicating that with the team.
The other challenge has been the balance of implementing solutions as well as making sure people are gaining skills in the project individually.
One obvious takeaway for me is that technical skills do not remove the need to be a compassionate person willing to help people in your team.
I feel studying for a technical field may have created a bias towards valuing people based on skills.
This meant at one point I thought that I would enjoy working with the most technical people.
However, I've realised that I enjoy working with good people who are enthusiastic about the work they do and have a healthy respect towards each other.
I feel that this project has taught me a lot so far and will hopefully lead to me being a better team mate in the future.
Overall
